# Read Project Docs First

Before planning or writing code, read the project docs in this order:

1. **`README.md`** — architecture, phased schedule, functional contracts, file layout
2. **`references/README.md`** — index of API docs; open only what the task needs
3. **`progress.md`** — what has already been done; avoid duplicating or contradicting prior work

## Which Reference to Open

| Task area | Read first |
|-----------|------------|
| Any module / phase | `references/autoos-api-mapping.md` |
| `gt_machine`, maintenance, shutdown | `references/OC-GTNH-docs-main/docs/components/gt_machine.lua`, `references/maintenance-and-safety.md` |
| ME inventory, crafting, fluids | `references/OC-GTNH-docs-main/docs/components/abstracts/CommonNetworkAPI.lua`, `me_interface.lua`, `type_definitions/ae_types/` |
| Component access, events, loops | `references/OC-GTNH-docs-main/docs/component.lua`, `event.lua`, `sides.lua` |
| GPU / monitoring UI | `references/OC-GTNH-docs-main/docs/components/gpu.lua`, `screen.lua` |
| Polling, tick budget, crashes | `references/performance-pitfalls.md` |
| GTNH adapter / MFU setup | `references/gtnh-opencomputers-overview.md` |
| General OC-GTNH docs | `references/OC-GTNH-docs-main/docs/` |
## Non-Negotiables (from docs)

- Modules read the **State Cache** only — never poll hardware directly
- Only the **Arbitrator** commits hardware changes (e.g. `setWorkAllowed()`)
- Maintenance: parse `getSensorInformation()` — no dedicated fault boolean
- Avoid `allItems()` in tight loops; prefer filtered `getItemsInNetwork()`
- Target tick overhead ≤ **500ms**

## Update progress.md After Every Change

After completing any task (code, docs, rules, config), **append** a new entry to `progress.md`:

- **Never rewrite or delete** existing entries — only add at the bottom
- One dated entry per logical change; list files created/modified and a one-line summary
- If a task spans multiple steps in one session, one combined entry is fine

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Short title

- Changed `path/to/file.lua`: what and why
- Added `path/to/new.lua`: purpose
```

## Example Workflow

```
❌ BAD: Jump straight into modules/process_control.lua and guess APIs

✅ GOOD:
1. Read README.md → confirm Phase 2 = hysteresis + inventory bands
2. Read references/autoos-api-mapping.md + OC-GTNH CommonNetworkAPI.lua
3. Read progress.md → see what's already implemented
4. Implement against documented APIs and architecture layers
5. Append entry to progress.md
```

Do not contradict README or references without explaining why and updating docs if the design changed.
